    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that feels like such a cope. like, \"resilient communities\" and \"tangible difference\" sounds so small when you look at the scale of what's actually happening. it's like trying to put out a forest fire with a water pistol. how can anyone actually find \"meaning\" in a world that's basically doomed? it just feels so futile.",
